reviews.text: Ein sehr gutes Steakhaus mit freundlicher, zuvorkommender, aber nicht aufdringlicher Bedienung. Der Chef macht einen sympathischen Eindruck. Die Karte liest sich gut und übersichtlich. Das von mir gewählte Ribeye Steak englisch auf heißem Stein war Weltklasse. Alle von uns gewählten Speisen waren sehr gut. Es war ein alles im allem sehr schöner Abend.

Sehr schönes Ambiente klein aber fein.
Gemütlich lädt zum vetweilen ein.
Preis Leistung stimmt.
Portionen ausreichend. 
Nette Bedienung kinderfreundlich
Bedienung sehr freundlich aber leider war das Fleisch total trocken. Der Preis war in Ordnung aber als steakhaus nicht zu empfehlen.
Die Speisen waren sehr lecker,  wenn es auch etwas länger gedauert hat.  Aber dafür kann man Verständnis haben, wenn man gesehen hat wie In Kellner gelaufen sind.

Das Essen und das Ambiente hat mir sehr gut gefallen, ist wirklich zu empfehlen. Parkplätze hinterm Haus auch sehr gut zu erreichen. Bisschen teuer aber die Speisekarte hat auch andere Gerichte die nicht sehr teuer sind also hingehen essen.
I have been here twice so far. Never disappointed. Always ordered steaks though.
Super place with perfectly baked steak!
I am sure here is mostly tasty steaks. Highly recommend this place for meat lovers!

Pricey but fantastic. There was no waiting time even though it was lunch time. The staff is really nice and helpful. They offered English menus right away and spoke English as well. The place itself is very cozy and has nice details that give it a great character of the wild west. The food was delicious and the portions were really big. Overall it is a great restaurant and I really recommend it!

I love this place we ordered their spring rolls definitely get the full appetizer. One is not enough. I could have eaten all eight by myself. They were definitely house made. Our waitress Sue actually helps make them. The staff spends hours making them. They fry them to order. My entree was amazing next time I'll get it at 3 stars of heat. My date got a curry dish and I liked it more than my noodle dish. For kids I would suggest the chicken appetizer with some rice and more spring rolls. The wait staff was amazing. Definitely will be going back and sending all of my friends and family.

It's located in the cozy popular 5 Points neighborhood which means parking is a bit limited. I ordered a cashew nut stirfry which was quite flavorful and Thai hot as I had hoped. 😊However, I ordered tofu as my protein with extra broccoli and the portions were disappointingly small even for a lunch menu. But I'm game to go again and check out the dinner menu and evening ambiance.
Delicious food, friendly and helpful service, great prices. The soups were excellent. I had spicy fried rice and thoroughly enjoyed it.
I've been going there since 1999. Same menu, same flavor, same location. Great place to try traditional Thai cuisine.

Ordered 2 pots of coconut soup, one w tofu and one w extra shrimp. The soup wasntwgood. It didn't have coconut taste. Tofu was tough, almost hard .The one w shrimp, had 6 med ones, also looks like broth from beef not coconut at all .Spri Sp rolls are smaller than before and hollow. Big waste of money. Since they changed hands, I guess they changed recipes. I don't like the change.
